%N A396462 Consider the square spiral in a single quadrant with its cells numbered starting at 0. Three players take turns and place black knights(K), cyan antelopes(A), and red ferzes(F), respectively, at the smallest unoccupied cell not attacked by an existing pieces of a different color. Sequence lists squares occupied by a cyan antelope.
%C A396462 A variant of A392177 with three players with different fairy chess pieces, and working in the first quadrant instead of the full Z X Z chessboard.
%H A396462 Sander G. Huisman, <a href="/A396462/b396462.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A396462 Brady Haran, Jonas Karlsson, and N. J. A. Sloane, <a href="https://youtu.be/UiX4CFIiegM">Red & Black Knights (extraordinary result)</a>;<a href="https://youtu.be/VgmDuBCayPw">Amazing Chessboard Patterns (extra)</a>, YouTube Numberphile videos, May 2026
%H A396462 Sander G. Huisman, <a href="/A396462/a396462.png">Image of the first 10^5 grid positions.</a>
%H A396462 Sander G. Huisman, <a href="/A396462/a396462_1.png">Image of the first 10^6 grid positions.</a>
%H A396462 Sander G. Huisman, <a href="/A396462/a396462_2.png">Image of the first 10^7 grid positions.</a>
%H A396462 Sander G. Huisman, <a href="/A396462/a396462_3.png">Image of the first 10^8 grid positions.</a>
%e A396462 The grid is as follows:
%e A396462   0  1  8  9  24 25
%e A396462   3  2  7  10 23 26
%e A396462   4  5  6  11 22 27
%e A396462   15 14 13 12 21 .
%e A396462   16 17 18 19 20 .
%e A396462   .  .  .  .  .  .
%e A396462 And gets occupied as follows:
%e A396462   K A . A . K
%e A396462   K F K K . A
%e A396462   F K . A K .
%e A396462   A . F K . A
%e A396462   . F K F A K
%e A396462   . A . F . F
%e A396462 Where the . means that the position remains unoccupied.
%Y A396462 Cf. A392182, A392183, A396461, A396463, A396465.
